community outreach login calendar giving contact us search friday march 16 2012 11 37 pm pdt community outreach ethics is not only a set of ideas it is also a practice among our practical activities we sponsor public lectures on topics such as the ethics of food and the environment the connection between stress and cheating the benefits and disadvantages of charter schools and the crisis of mass incarceration that is currently facing our nation among other topics our events are free and open to the public and we invite you to join us to receive email announcements of our events email joan berry in addition to sponsoring talks panel discussions and conferences we are involved in ongoing community partnerships we are very proud of our association with the hope house scholars program and with the palo alto unified school district to name two of our ongoing efforts along with our community partners our center explores issues of justice and injustice tolerance and respect right and wrong citizenship and community looking for new opportunities we are always interested in partnering with local organizations to explore issues of justice and injustice tolerance and respect right and wrong citizenship and community if you would like to suggest an organization collaboration email joan berry home about people events undergraduate program working papers grants & fellowships community outreach hope house palo alto unified school district alumni outreach news & announcements audio video & publications bowen h mccoy family center for ethics in society 559 nathan abbott way stanford ca 94305 8610 650 736 2629 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved feedback terms of use site map helpsu
